{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Added --ref/--source to all 5 CLI commands (_llm_commands.py: _review/_review_code/_scan_spec/_verify_completion/_review_plan via shared _add_ref_source) AND the 5 MCP tools (mcp_server.py: review_ticket/review_code/scan_spec/verify_completion/review_plan), one-to-one. AC1 pinned CLI<->MCP mapping (no naming drift), proven by an MCP list_tools inputSchema introspection test + per-command CLI threading test; AC2 defaults None->config-resolved (origin/main+attested; review-code ref defaults to the reviewed head), local reachable on both surfaces + reflected unsigned; AC3 verified_at_sha surfaced (JSON passes it through; text via _render_source_line); AC4 invalid --source -> argparse exit 2, unresolvable/absent ref + unreachable object DB -> SnapshotError caught -> clean Error + exit 1 (attested fails closed); AC5 cwd/branch decoupling covered by the S3 regression (REBAR_ROOT only locates the object DB); AC6 vertical slice (review-ticket end-to-end) validated first. Subagent review: NO blocking issues, all 6 ACs met; folded its finding (review-code --ref help no longer overstates REBAR_GATE_REF configurability). 6 S5 tests + 569 mcp/cli/llm tests green (1 pre-existing @integration jira test unrelated); ruff clean."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782544231613040001,"uuid":"e9575e3d-42ad-471c-abd8-a0a9cfa974ad"}